@startuml
title Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) - Conceptual Flow

actor Victim
participant "Victim Browser" as Browser
participant "Trusted Web Application" as WebApp
participant "Attacker Website" as Attacker

Victim ->> WebApp: Login with credentials
WebApp ->> Browser: Session cookie stored

Victim -> Attacker: Visit malicious webpage
Attacker --> Browser: Send hidden request (e.g., auto-submitting form)

Browser -> WebApp: Send request with session cookie
WebApp -> WebApp: Process request as authenticated user
WebApp --> Browser: Action completed (e.g., change settings, transfer funds)

note over Browser
Browser automatically
includes stored cookies
with the request
end note

note over WebApp
Server cannot distinguish
between legitimate user action
and forged request
end note

@enduml